  "description": "Home sprouting became popular as a low-cost, year-round source of fresh food. Microgreens followed as a kitchen-scale adaptation of greenhouse baby greens. Food-safety guidance tightened over time as sprout-related outbreaks highlighted the need for careful rinsing and sanitation.",
